snippet.textDisplay:
I've deleted tons of tweets. Before I post; I read the tweet. Then after posting; I read it again. And sometimes I still make a spelling error, so I copy the tweet's text, delete the tweet, make a new tweet in which I paste the previous tweet's text, and then change it so there's no spelling mistakes or incorrect URLs.

Look there's a website I usually go to when I need a cable of any kind (power, fiber, network, audio, etc etc) and while I don't always buy there (they're not always the cheapest), what I love about the website is that after you order it gives you a 15 minute window to order something else which will be added to your existing order for free (so no additional send costs or contacting their helpdesk when you forget that one thing like a moron). I've only used it once, but it's pretty great and Twitter needs a minute or more grace period as well where you can just safely edit it.
